The paper discusses the challenges and advancements in automated vulnerability detection and exploit generation in computer systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the need for building automated analysis systems, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The Cyber Grand Challenge (CGC) competition, which is the focus of the paper, involves systems that perform automated reasoning and decision-making, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the underlying technologies and related works, which involves programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
